rComments: She knows her stuff and covered a lot of different ideas for each play. I wish there was more class discussion but the class was dead quiet.

She is a very poor marker. Completely arbitrary in her marking. Very unfair. It was clear she had not read my paper. No comments on the paper - just a random, non-sensical mark. She gave the same mark to my friend whose paper was incomplete and basically incoherent. A PhD student read my paper and said I deserved a much higher mark. Marred my GPA.
She's passionate about plays and films and she cares about what students have to say. I like the group work - a seminar class with her would be perfect.
This class (Comedy) is so much fun!  The room is too hot, but Prof. Papoutsis keeps things interesting and you look at the plays in ways you wouldn't expect.
